                <p>
                  <strong>1.</strong> Convert start and end times to minutes
                  since midnight.
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>2.</strong> If end &lt; start, assume the shift ends
                  the next day:
                </p>
                <p>
                  <code
                    >durationMinutes = (endMinutes + 24 × 60) −
                    startMinutes</code
                  >
                </p>
                <p><strong>3.</strong> Subtract unpaid breaks:</p>
                <p>
                  <code
                    >netMinutes = max(0, durationMinutes − breakMinutes)</code
                  >
                </p>
                <p><strong>4.</strong> Convert to hours:</p>
                <p><code>hours = netMinutes / 60</code></p>
              </div>

              <h3>Overtime calculation</h3>
              <p>
                When you enter an overtime threshold and multiplier, the
                calculator splits your hours into regular and overtime:
              </p>
              <div class="formula-box text-sm">
                <p><code>regularHours = min(totalHours, otThreshold)</code></p>
                <p><code>otHours = max(0, totalHours − otThreshold)</code></p>
                <p>
                  <code
                    >pay = hourlyRate × regularHours + hourlyRate × otMultiplier
                    × otHours</code
                  >
                </p>
              </div>
